2.1.1.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute h_joint_disorders from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • some hedibX == 3 into 1
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • otherwise into 0

To compute h_joint_disorders_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if h_joint_disorders == 1, h_joint_disorders_age = heagf
  • if h_joint_disorders == 0, h_joint_disorders_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • otherwise, h_joint_disorders_age = 999

R script:

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w1 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w1$id)
ELSA_ds_w1$h_joint_disorders <- rep(0, length(ELSA_w1$id))
ELSA_ds_w1$h_joint_disorders[which((ELSA_w1$hedib01 == 3 | ELSA_w1$hedib02 == 
    3 | ELSA_w1$hedib03 == 3 | ELSA_w1$hedib04 == 3 | ELSA_w1$hedib05 == 3 | 
    ELSA_w1$hedib06 == 3 | ELSA_w1$hedib07 == 3 | ELSA_w1$hedib08 == 3 | ELSA_w1$hedib09 == 
    3 | ELSA_w1$hedib10 == 3))] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w1$h_joint_disorders[which(ELSA_w1$hedib01 == -9)] <- 997
ELSA_ds_w1$h_joint_disorders[which(ELSA_w1$hedib01 == -8)] <- 998

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w1$h_joint_disorders_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w1$id))
ELSA_ds_w1$h_joint_disorders_age[which(ELSA_ds_w1$h_joint_disorders == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w1$h_joint_disorders_age[which(ELSA_ds_w1$h_joint_disorders == 1)] <- car::recode(ELSA_w1$heagf[which(ELSA_ds_w1$h_joint_disorders == 
    1)], "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997")

# Global table
ELSA_ds <- ELSA_ds_w1

2.1.2.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute h_joint_disorders from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • h_joint_disorders w1 == 1 or some hedibX == 3 into 1
  • h_joint_disorders w1 != 1 and hedib01 == -9 into 997
  • h_joint_disorders w1 != 1 and hedib01 == -8 into 998
  • otherwise into 0

To compute h_joint_disorders_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if h_joint_disorders == 1, h_joint_disorders_age = HeAgf
  • if h_joint_disorders == 0, h_joint_disorders_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • otherwise, h_joint_disorders_age = 999

R script:

ELSA_w2 <- left_join(ELSA_w2, ELSA_ds, by = "id")

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w2 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w2$id)
ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders <- rep(0, length(ELSA_w2$id))
ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders[which(ELSA_w2$h_joint_disorders == 1 | ((ELSA_w2$hedib01 == 
    3 | ELSA_w2$hedib02 == 3 | ELSA_w2$hedib03 == 3 | ELSA_w2$hedib04 == 3)))] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders[which((ELSA_w2$h_joint_disorders != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w2$h_joint_disorders)) & 
    ELSA_w2$hedib01 == -9)] <- 997
ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders[which((ELSA_w2$h_joint_disorders != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w2$h_joint_disorders)) & 
    ELSA_w2$hedib01 == -8)] <- 998

# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w2$id))
ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders_age[which(ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders_age[which(ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders == 1)] <- car::recode(ELSA_w2$HeAgf[which(ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders == 
    1)], "-1=996;-8=998;-9=997")
ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders_age[which(ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders == 1 & !is.na(ELSA_w2$h_joint_disorders_age) & 
    !ELSA_w2$h_joint_disorders_age %in% miss_values_vector)] <- ELSA_w2$h_joint_disorders_age[which(ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders == 
    1 & !is.na(ELSA_w2$h_joint_disorders_age) & !ELSA_w2$h_joint_disorders_age %in% 
    miss_values_vector)]

# Update of global table
assign_merge <- function(endtib, sttib, log_vec = c(T), col_end_index = NULL, 
    col_st_index = NULL) {
    newtib <- full_join(endtib, sttib, by = "id")
    row.names(newtib) <- newtib$id
    newtib[log_vec, col_end_index] <- newtib[log_vec, col_st_index]
    id_ind <- match("id", names(newtib))
    newtib <- newtib[, c(id_ind, col_end_index)]
    names(newtib)[2] <- "x"
    newtib$x <- car::recode(newtib$x, "NA=999")
    names(newtib)[2] <- names(endtib)[col_end_index]
    newtib
}
ELSA_ds_prov <- ELSA_ds[, c(1, 2)]
ELSA_ds_prov <- assign_merge(ELSA_ds_prov, ELSA_ds_w2, log_vec = ELSA_ds_w2$id, 
    col_end_index = 2, col_st_index = 3)
ELSA_ds_aux <- ELSA_ds[, c(1, 3)]
ELSA_ds_aux <- assign_merge(ELSA_ds_aux, ELSA_ds_w2, log_vec = ELSA_ds_w2$id[which(ELSA_ds_w2$h_joint_disorders != 
    999)], col_end_index = 2, col_st_index = 4)
ELSA_ds <- ELSA_ds_prov
ELSA_ds$h_joint_disorders_age <- ELSA_ds_aux$h_joint_disorders_age
rm(ELSA_ds_prov)
rm(ELSA_ds_aux)

2.1.3.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute h_joint_disorders from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • h_joint_disorders previous == 1 or dhedibar == 1 into 1
  • h_joint_disorders previous == 0 and dhedibar == 0 into 0
  • dhedibar == -1 into 996
  • otherwise into 999

To compute h_joint_disorders_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if h_joint_disorders == 1, h_joint_disorders_age = heagf
  • if h_joint_disorders == 0, h_joint_disorders_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • otherwise, h_joint_disorders_age = 999

2.1.4.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute h_joint_disorders from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • h_joint_disorders previous == 1 or hedibar == 1 into 1
  • h_joint_disorders previous == 0 and hedibar == 0 into 0
  • hedibar == -1 into 996
  • hedibar == -9 into 997
  • hedibar == -8 into 998
  • otherwise into 999

To compute h_joint_disorders_age from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if h_joint_disorders == 1, h_joint_disorders_age = heagf
  • if h_joint_disorders == 0, h_joint_disorders_age = 996
  • -9 into 997
  • -8 into 998
  • -2 into 991
  • -1 into 996
  • otherwise, h_joint_disorders_age = 999

R script:

ELSA_w4 <- left_join(ELSA_w4, ELSA_ds, by = "id")

# Categorical variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w4 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w4$id)
ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w4$id))
ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders[which((ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders)) & 
    (ELSA_w4$hedibar == 0))] <- 0
ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders[which(ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders == 1 | (ELSA_w4$hedibar == 
    1))] <- 1
ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders[which((ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders)) & 
    ELSA_w4$hedibar == -1)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders[which((ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders)) & 
    ELSA_w4$hedibar == -9)] <- 997
ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders[which((ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders != 1 | is.na(ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders)) & 
    ELSA_w4$hedibar == -8)] <- 998


# Continuous variable harmonization
ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders_age <- rep(999, length(ELSA_w4$id))
ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders == 0)] <- 996
ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders == 1)] <- car::recode(ELSA_w4$heagf[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders == 
    1)], "-1=996;-2=991;-8=998;-9=997")
ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders == 1 & !is.na(ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders_age) & 
    !ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders_age %in% miss_values_vector)] <- ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders_age[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders == 
    1 & !is.na(ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders_age) & !ELSA_w4$h_joint_disorders_age %in% 
    miss_values_vector)]

# Update of global table
assign_merge <- function(endtib, sttib, log_vec = c(T), col_end_index = NULL, 
    col_st_index = NULL) {
    newtib <- full_join(endtib, sttib, by = "id")
    row.names(newtib) <- newtib$id
    newtib[log_vec, col_end_index] <- newtib[log_vec, col_st_index]
    id_ind <- match("id", names(newtib))
    newtib <- newtib[, c(id_ind, col_end_index)]
    names(newtib)[2] <- "x"
    newtib$x <- car::recode(newtib$x, "NA=999")
    names(newtib)[2] <- names(endtib)[col_end_index]
    newtib
}
ELSA_ds_prov <- ELSA_ds[, c(1, 2)]
ELSA_ds_prov <- assign_merge(ELSA_ds_prov, ELSA_ds_w4, log_vec = ELSA_ds_w4$id, 
    col_end_index = 2, col_st_index = 3)
ELSA_ds_aux <- ELSA_ds[, c(1, 3)]
ELSA_ds_aux <- assign_merge(ELSA_ds_aux, ELSA_ds_w4, log_vec = ELSA_ds_w4$id[which(ELSA_ds_w4$h_joint_disorders != 
    999)], col_end_index = 2, col_st_index = 4)
ELSA_ds <- ELSA_ds_prov
ELSA_ds$h_joint_disorders_age <- ELSA_ds_aux$h_joint_disorders_age
rm(ELSA_ds_prov)
rm(ELSA_ds_aux)
